column1: This .csv file has been created as a one-off extraction on 2020-08-20.
Some users have been differencing the data_covid19_msis_by_location_YYYY-MM-DD
data series to create "municipality-level time-series". These users have requested
that we provide historical data to bridge the gap between 2020-02-28 and data_covid19_msis_by_location_2020-06-04
This dataset fulfills that request.
An example of interpreting the data correctly follows below.
When we look at Oslo (municip0301) we find the following values:
data_covid19_msis_by_location_2020-06-19.csv (i.e. a snapshot of MSIS at 2020-06-19 00:00)
data_covid19_msis_by_location_2020-06-18.csv (i.e. a snapshot of MSIS at 2020-06-18 00:00)
We can therefore conclude that 5 people from Oslo were registered in MSIS on 2020-06-18.
This is confirmed in this dataset below: 2020-06-18
It is important to note that differencing the data_covid19_msis_by_location_YYYY-MM-DD
data series (and by using this historical dataset) will create a time-series where
the data corresponds to "number of people registered in MSIS on this date".
This is not the same as the time-series provided in the data_covid19_msis_by_time_location_YYYY-MM-DD
time series
